16/03/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- Albania has supplied the Irish Republican Army (IRA) with weapons, local media reported on Sunday (March 15th), quoting reports in UK newspapers. The IRA reportedly imported weapons, including assault rifles and handguns, from Albania. An investigation by Irish security services reportedly revealed the name of the supplier. (Top News, News 24, Shekulli, Top Channel, Sunday Times - 15/03/09) 
